JOHANNESBURG (AP) — India captain Virat Kohli was ruled out of the second test in South Africa on the morning of the game with a back injury as the tourists won the toss and opted to bat first on Monday.K.L. Rahul will stand in for Kohli as captain. Rahul said at the toss that Kohli had an upper back spasm and couldn’t play.It’s a crucial game as top-ranked India, which leads the three-test series 1-0, goes in search of its first test series win in South Africa. India has a strong record at the Wanderers in Johannesburg to boost its chance of history.Hanuma Vihari came in to the team for Kohli in India’s only change from the 113-run victory in Centurion.South Africa made two changes, with Kyle Verreynne in as wicketkeeper for Quinton de Kock. De Kock was due to miss the rest of the series anyway for the birth of his first child but made a shock announcement at the end of the first test last week that he was retiring from test cricket at the age of 29.ADVERTISEMENTSportsPackers rout Vikings 37-10 in cold to take NFC's No. 1 seedBrown walks away from Bucs; Brady rallies team past JetsCards hold off Cowboys 25-22 in matchup of playoff teamsBills clinch playoff berth, eliminate Falcons with 29-15 winIn South Africa’s other change, fast bowler Duanne Olivier was recalled for his first test in three years after putting on hold his international career to play county cricket in England. ___Lineups:South Africa: Dean Elgar (captain), Aiden Markram, Keegan Petersen, Rassie van der Dussen, Temba Bavuma, Kyle Verreynne, Marco Jansen, Kagiso Rabada, Keshav Maharaj, Duanne Olivier, Lungi Ngidi.India: Mayank Agarwal, K.L. Rahul (captain), Cheteshwar Pujara, Ajinkya Rahane, Hanuma Vihari, Rishabh Pant, Ravichandran Ashwin, Shardul Thakur, Mohammed Shami, Japsrit Bumrah, Mohammed Siraj.___More AP cricket: https://apnews.com/hub/cricket and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports